5a.	Lore delivery for locations

5b.	Uldim Pass / Summerbridge

	Uldim Pass receives heavy snows in winter, closing
	it to travel.  During the winter months there is
	no passable route between Antresk and Mt. Uldim.
	During the spring season of Snowmelt Uldim Pass
	again becomes open for passage.

	Snows begin falling on Uldim Pass during the month
	of Waning days.  Travelers caught in Uldim Pass when
	it closes will be trapped there until spring.


	The lands of Summerbridge receive heavy seasonal rains
	beginning in the fall, making them unpassable.  From
	fall through spring the lands of Aethelarn and Caburh
	in the south are cut off from East and West Urvil in
	the north.  Only when the heat of summer comes do the
	swamps dry enough to permit passage.

	Travelers caught in Summerbridge when the rains begin
	in the first month of fall will find themselves trapped
	in the swamps until the following summer.


