By the way, Marquis is the more normal form of spelling Marquess.
The British corrupt many french words, and marquess is the
literal spelling for the corrupted pronunciation, but most
enlightened folks can pronounce Marquis correctly, especially us
Americans who love the frogs, except when NATO is involved.

