>There's not a lot of science, no.  If you have some ideas along these
>lines, feel free to propose them.  I am always open to new skill
>categories.

Hmm...  If I was going to mix technology in with magic, I would do so in a
19th Centry style, or better yet, more fantastical, as in Jules Verne. 
(OK, maybe i would put a hidden ciy somewhere with a crashed space probe
with a functioning AI ;-)

What I would think of adding to the game would be a new building type of
University.  And you could have Depts. of 

  - Biology/Druidicism, could be a whole complement to the Magic system
  - Engineering (IMHO- the construction skill is sort of unfounded, you
just don't learn engineering principles in seven days).  In game terms,
would effect percetages:  how long to build, chance to a mine collapsing,
etc.  Special skill of tunnelling to collapse castle walls.
  - Minerology - increase yields of mining.  Advanced skill of smelting if
you want to introduce more advanced metals which leads to better weapons.
  - Literature - steering public opinion???  (If you ever played Midgard,
there was the idea that you carried a "reputation" with you, good, bad, or
unknown)  It could also affect recruiting.
  - Commerce - percentage affecting your buy/sell price and quantity.

Hmm...  where I seem to be leading is a way to get a skill that alters the
percentages of "yield" of other skills by having an educations.

Whatcha think?



